title: Obolensky: Byzantium and the slavs (1971 edition)
description:
Please download first the sample pages in order to decide if the quality of the scan is enough for you.










This book pertains to a past epoch in which migrations and macro-culture ethnic features was the all explaining clinching , but nobody whith interest in the deep roots of both Russia and medieval Europe can afford to miss.


If the russian joke says that the KGV invented a machine to knnow with detail the future , but the problem remains the past , just because is always changing , in nowhere but the balkans , Turkey and Russia is the IDENTITY question more pressing a question.
